{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TrCzqohKVcSn7VVFtRWdQK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've retrieved all the files you requested. Here's the full contents:\n\n## 1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts`\n\nThis file defines the coinflip create endpoint handler. Key patterns:\n- Uses Hono framework with async route handlers\n- Validates request body with custom validation function\n- Generates server secret and commitment\n- Derives match PDA\n- Checks for duplicates in DB\n- Builds and partially-signs transaction\n- Stores round in DB with phase \"created\"\n- Writes operator event for audit trail\n- Returns transaction, matchPda, and commitment\n\nThe route handler interface accepts `CreateRoutesDeps` with `db`, `connection`, and `serverKeypair`.\n\n## 2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\nThe main app entry point. Key patterns:\n- Initializes config, db, and connection\n- Creates Hono app\n- Adds `/health` endpoint\n- Applies rate limiting middleware to `/fairness/*` routes\n- Applies auth middleware to `/fairness/*` routes\n- Routes `/fairness/coinflip` to the coinflip routes\n- Starts settlement worker with retry-aware settler\n- Exports default handler for serverless deployment\n\nRoutes are mounted with `app.route(\"/path\", createSomeRoutes(deps))`\n\n## 3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\nDatabase client module with comprehensive types and functions:\n\n**Types:**\n- `RoundPhase`: \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\"\n- `OperatorEventType`: various event types for audit logging\n- `Round`: full round record with all fields (pda, game, creator, secret, commitment, tier, side, nonce, phase, settle tracking, result data)\n- `InsertRoundParams`: parameters for inserting a new round\n- `OperatorEvent`: audit log record\n\n**Phase Transitions:**\n- created → locked, expired\n- locked → settling\n- settling → settled\n- settled and expired are terminal states\n\n**Db Interface Methods:**\n- `insertRound()`: Insert new round, throws on duplicate PDA\n- `updateRoundPhase()`: Transition phase with optional field updates\n- `getRoundByPda()`: Get round by PDA (returns undefined if not found)\n- `getRoundsByPhase()`: Get all rounds in a phase\n- `insertOperatorEvent()`: Log operator events\n- `close()`: Close connection pool\n\nUses `postgres` library (sql template literals) for queries.\n\n## 4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n\nConfiguration loader. Key patterns:\n\n**Config Interface:**\n- `port`: Server port (default 3100)\n- `databaseUrl`: Required env var\n- `rpcUrl`: Required env var\n- `serverKeypair`: Keypair from JSON env var\n- `authClockSkewSeconds`: Clock skew tolerance (default 60)\n- `rateLimitPerWallet`: Requests per wallet (default 10)\n- `rateLimitGlobal`: Global limit (default 100)\n- `workerPollIntervalMs`: Worker polling interval (default 2000)\n- `entropyAccount`: Entropy source account (default system program)\n\nUses `requireEnv()` helper for required vars and `parseKeypair()` for Keypair parsing.\n\n---\n\nNow you have all the patterns you need to create `src/routes/rounds.ts`. The structure shows:\n1. Define route handler interface with deps (`Db`, `Connection`, etc.)\n2. Create route factory function returning Hono app\n3. Define request body types and validation\n4. Implement endpoints with try-catch error handling\n5. Use db methods like `getRoundByPda()`, `getRoundsByPhase()`, `updateRoundPhase()`\n6. Return JSON responses with appropriate status codes\n7. Log operator events for audit trail"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af2f7aae8f262861c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40450\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 34437</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"da7de446-89c1-4a